J. EDWIN LARSON, as State Treasurer of the State of Florida, and Ex-Officio Insurance Commissioner of said State, v. VOLUNTEER STATE LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY, a corporation organized and existing under the laws of the State of Florida. 12 So. (2nd) 898

January Term, 1943

April 13, 1943 Division A Rehearing Denied May 3, 1943 J. Tom Watson, Attorney General, and Lewis W. Petteway, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. Oven, Stanley & Oven, W. J. Oven and B. C. Stanley, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

The decree appealed from in the case at bar is hereby reversed for further proceedings in the lower court not inconsistent with and upon the authority of State ex rel. Pacific Mutual Life Insurance Co. v. Larson, et al., 152 Fla. 729, 12 So. (2nd) 896, this day decided.

It is so ordered.

BUFORD, C. J., TERRELL, CHAPMAN and ADAMS, JJ., concur.
